==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peep sight
<hw>Peep sight</hw>. <def>An adjustable piece, pierced with a small hole
to peep through in aiming, attached to a rifle or other firearm near the
breech; -- distinguished from an <contr>open sight</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peepul tree</ent>⟦br⟧
